OL,3,CEmergency staff aiming for Guinness
OL,4,CWorld Record in online CPR lessons
OL,6,FLee Myers, a Paramedic Team Lead, says
OL,7,Fthe CPR event aims to show how anyone
OL,8,Fcan learn a lifesaving skill.
OL,10,FHe said: "Anyone can do this. No
OL,11,Fmanikin is required. All you need is a
OL,12,Fjacket to roll up into a ball. A
OL,13,Fpillow... anything you feel you can
OL,14,Fpractice CPR, that's all you need to
OL,15,Ftake part today."
OL,17,FThe sessions, which started at 9am and
OL,18,Fwill end in the evening of 10 October
OL,19,F2024, will also include advice on
OL,20,Fdefibrillators and 999 calls.
